      talk:"\"Every detection on this screen was written by the Counter Threat Unit — the same team that tracks nation-state threat actors, publishes adversary profiles, and provides intelligence to law enforcement globally. These are not community-sourced rules or generic Sigma detections. They are rules built from direct observation of real adversary campaigns in customer environments worldwide. Over 1,000 of them, continuously updated as the CTU identifies new techniques. And because Taegis normalises all incoming telemetry to a common schema, a detection rule written to catch credential access behaviour fires against CrowdStrike telemetry, Sophos Endpoint telemetry, Palo Alto firewall logs, and Okta identity events simultaneously. One rule. Every source. That is the cross-domain detection story.\"",
