      id:"xdr_rules",
      name:"Rules",
      preview:"CTU detection rule library — browse, customise, suppress, and create custom detection rules",
      what:"The Rules screen provides visibility into and management of the Taegis detection rule library — showing all active CTU-maintained detection rules, allowing administrators to suppress specific rules for known false positive scenarios, tune rule sensitivity, and create custom detection rules using the Taegis rule language for organisation-specific threat scenarios not covered by the CTU library. Custom rules apply across all ingested telemetry sources using the same normalised schema as CTU rules.",
      talk:"\"Rules gives you both visibility into what the CTU is detecting on your behalf and the ability to extend that coverage with your own organisation-specific logic. The CTU library covers the broad threat landscape — common adversary techniques, known malware families, suspicious behavioral patterns observed across thousands of customer environments. But every organisation has unique context: a service account that legitimately performs actions that look like credential access, or a specific internal tool that generates network patterns that trigger false positives. Rules lets you suppress those known exceptions without disabling broad detection categories. And custom rules let you add detection logic specific to your environment — a rule that fires when a specific internal system is accessed outside business hours, for example.\"",
