      talk:"\"People gives you the user-centric view of mobile security — which matters when a single user has multiple devices. A sales executive might have a corporate iPhone and a personal Android both accessing corporate email. People shows you both, their compliance states, and any threat activity attributed to that user. It is also the starting point for BYOD enrollment campaigns. You select a group of users and send them a self-enrollment invitation with a link and a QR code. The user clicks the link on their personal device, follows a guided enrollment flow, and their device appears in your console within minutes — with the correct BYOD policy applied automatically.\"",
