      talk:"\"Policies are what make MDM valuable beyond just knowing which devices are enrolled. A Wi-Fi policy silently configures corporate SSID credentials on every enrolled device — users connect automatically without IT sharing a Wi-Fi password. A VPN policy pushes your corporate VPN profile with per-app configuration so only corporate apps route through the VPN — not personal browser traffic. An email policy configures the corporate Exchange or M365 account on every device automatically. All of this happens silently in the background when the device checks in. The user opens their phone, their corporate email is configured, Wi-Fi connects automatically, VPN is ready — without calling the helpdesk once.\"",
