      preview:"App management — silent app push, mandatory and optional apps, app blocklist, VPP and ABM integration",
      what:"The Apps section manages the app catalogue for enrolled devices — silently pushing mandatory apps to all devices in a group, making optional apps available via self-service catalogue, blocking prohibited apps, and managing app licences through Apple Business Manager VPP and Android Enterprise managed Google Play. Apps are pushed without requiring user Apple ID or Google account credentials on corporate-owned devices.",
      talk:"\"App management closes one of the most painful gaps in mobile management — getting apps onto corporate devices without requiring users to enter personal credentials. With Apple Business Manager and Volume Purchase Programme integrated, I can silently push any licensed app to every corporate iPhone in a group without the user ever entering their personal Apple ID or agreeing to App Store terms. The app appears on their home screen automatically. For Android Enterprise, apps come from managed Google Play with the same silent push capability. For BYOD, mandatory apps appear as notifications the user accepts — and if they remove a mandatory app, Sophos flags the device as non-compliant automatically.\"",
      points:[
        "Silent app push — mandatory apps deployed to devices without user interaction or personal account credentials via ABM VPP or Android Enterprise",
        "Prohibited app blocking — flag or block specific apps or app categories; device marked non-compliant if a prohibited app is installed",
        "Apple Business Manager integration — VPP licence management for paid apps; push, revoke, and reassign licences centrally",
        "BYOD app compliance — mandatory apps flagged as required on BYOD devices; non-installation triggers compliance violation"
      ],
      action:"Navigate to Apps. Show the app list and filter to mandatory apps. Show how a mandatory app is assigned to a device group. Demonstrate the Apple Business Manager VPP integration if available. Show a prohibited app rule and explain how it triggers a compliance violation. Show the self-service app catalogue available to BYOD users."
