  objections:[
    {q:"We use Microsoft Intune — why add Sophos Mobile?",a:"The relevant conversation for Intune customers is Mobile Threat Defense, not MDM replacement. Sophos MTD integrates with Intune via the Mobile Threat Defense connector: threat signals (malicious app, network attack, jailbreak) are sent to Intune for conditional access decisions. Keep Intune for management, add Sophos for active threat detection. You get the best of both without replacing your existing investment."},
    {q:"We can't put software on personal devices.",a:"Containerized BYOD enrollment deploys a secure work container — not a full MDM agent. The user's personal data, apps, and photos are completely untouched. IT manages the corporate container only. The only policy applying to the personal side is screen lock — which users accept because it protects their own device. Enrollment takes 5 minutes with no IT involvement required."}
  ],
