      id:"wifi_apxsettings",
      name:"APX Settings",
      preview:"Advanced AP configuration — transmit power, channel width, band steering, roaming, MESH settings",
      what:"APX Settings provides advanced wireless radio configuration for the Sophos AP6 and APX access point series — including transmit power settings, channel width selection (20/40/80/160MHz), band steering aggressiveness, fast roaming configuration (802.11r), client load balancing, and wireless mesh configuration for AP-to-AP backhaul where wired PoE runs are not possible. These settings tune wireless performance beyond the default configuration for demanding enterprise environments.",
      talk:"\"APX Settings is where you tune the wireless environment beyond the defaults for high-density or high-performance requirements. In an open-plan office with 50 devices per AP, you might reduce transmit power and channel width to reduce co-channel interference and improve per-device throughput. In a warehouse with long distances between APs, you increase transmit power and use wider channels for maximum range. 802.11r fast roaming is configured here — critical for voice-over-Wi-Fi environments where a 500ms roaming delay breaks a call. And wireless mesh lets you backhaul AP-to-AP wirelessly where running Ethernet cable to every location is not feasible.\"",
